name: electric motor production, vehicle (electric powertrain) | electric motor, electric passenger car | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/1670/documentation

This dataset describes an electric motor used for an electric passenger car. It is based on direct information from the Swiss manufacturer Brusa. The electric motor has a maximal output power of about 100kW The entries are given as a function of kg device. The specific motor which was used for this dataset weights 53 kg.

The dataset starts with reception of  the raw materials and the electronic components used in the inverter, the efforts needed for the production of the components as well as the assembly of the motor.

The activity returns the fully assmebled motor and as by-products the scrap fractions coming from the production process.
category: C:Manufacturing/27:Manufacture of electrical equipment/271:Manufacture of electric motors, generators, transformers and electricity distribution and control apparatus/2710:Manufacture of electric motors, generators, transformers and electricity di

processDocumentation.technologyDescription: This dataset is based on current, high-level standard.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: The data has been gathered between 2010 and 2011 and is expected, due to the high quality of the manufacturer, to be representative at least until 2015.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Data on materials and technology has been provided directly by the Swiss manufacturer Brusa.

exchanges.description: This dataset is based on direct information from the Swiss manufacturer Brusa.
